paint(Graphics) - Method in class com.elveskevtar.divebomb.gfx.Game
The overriden paint method; this branches off into other paint methods based on the state variable.
paintGame(Graphics) - Method in class com.elveskevtar.divebomb.gfx.Game
Paints the general aspects of the actual game itself such as the players, names, projectiles, maps, and other images that are needed for every gamemode.
paintMap - Variable in class com.elveskevtar.divebomb.gfx.Game
The BufferedImage object corresponding to the actual graphical map that will be painted within the game.
paintPauseMenu(Graphics) - Method in class com.elveskevtar.divebomb.gfx.Game
This method is usually called immediately after calling public void paintGame(Graphics g) so that the pause menu serves as an overlay and gamemodes that do not pause, such as MP gamemodes, can continue in the background.
paintReconnect(Graphics) - Method in class com.elveskevtar.divebomb.gfx.Game
This method is usually called immediately after calling public void paintGame(Graphics g) so that the game is still painted underneath the reconnect screen which only serves as an overlay to notify the user of connection issues.
PAUSE_OVERLAY - Static variable in class com.elveskevtar.divebomb.gfx.Game
Corresponds to the RGBA value of 32, 32, 32, 100.
players - Variable in class com.elveskevtar.divebomb.gfx.Game

playerSize - Variable in class com.elveskevtar.divebomb.gfx.Game
The total number of players needed for a full game of a specific gamemode.
